The paper proposes a deep learning approach for localizing prostate landmarks in ultrasound images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach is specifically designed for medical imaging applications, which suggests the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.Medical Imaging). The paper also mentions the use of multitask learning and adversarial training, which are popular techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
